title: 15 Chess Books - April 2016 (gnv64)
description:
This is a collection of 15 chess books, 14 PDFs & 1 ePUB:


01. Chess Tactics For Advanced Players by Yuri Averbakh
02. Chess The Complete Guide (4th Ed) by Logan Donovan
03. Chess Training Pocket Book - 300 Most Important Positions and Ideas (2nd Ed) by Lev Alburt
04. Chess Traveller's Quiz Book by Julian Hogdson
05. Critical Moments in Chess by Pata Gaprindashvili
06. Jon Speelman's Best Games by Jonathan Speelman
07. Mastering the Modern Benoni and the Benko Gambit by Robert Bellin, Pietro Ponzetto
08. Revolutionize Your Chess by Victor Moskalenko
09. Starting Out: Rook Endgames by Chris Ward
10. Tal's Winning Chess Combinations by Mikhail Tal, Victor Khenkin
11. Test and Improve Your Chess by Lev Alburt
12. Invisible Chess Moves - Discover Your Blind Spots and Stop Overlooking Simple Wins
13. The Open Games for Black by Igor Lysyj, Roman Ovetchkin
14. The Open Spanish by Mikhail Krasenkov
15. The World Chess Crown Challenge - Kasparov vs Karpov Seville '87 by David Bronstein
